astructure build-out has resulted in significant operating losses (Q1 2026 AI loss from operations of $(2,469) million; FY 2025 loss of $(6,355) million) driven by cloud computing costs, data center operating expenses, and GPU hardware depreciation.\n\n### 3. Data Center Capital Expenditures (Q1 2026 and FY 2025)\n*Note: The provided text does not isolate "Data Center CapEx" as a standalone line item separate from the AI Segment or Total CapEx. However, the AI Segment CapEx serves as the direct proxy, as the MD&A explicitly attributes AI CapEx increases to data center build-outs.*\n\n*   **Q1 2026 AI/Data Center CapEx:** **$7,723 million** (out of $10,107 million Total Company CapEx).\n*   **FY 2025 AI/Data Center CapEx:** **$12,727 million** (out of $20,737 million Total Company CapEx).\n*   **Capitalized Interest:** The company capitalizes interest during the construction period for significant long-term projects, specifically naming **"AI infrastructure data centers."** ($7 million was capitalized in Q1 2026 and added to Construction-in-progress).\n\n**Related PP&E Asset Balances (Note 5):**\nThe scale of the data center investments is further reflected in the company\'s gross Property, Plant, and Equipment balances:\n*   **Servers and networking equipment:** $23,850 million (Mar 31, 2026) / $22,694 million (Dec 31, 2025)\n*   **Data center infrastructure:** $2,965 million (Mar 31, 2026) / $2,960 million (Dec 31, 2025)\n*   **Construction-in-progress (CIP):** **$14,045 million** (Mar 31, 2026) / $4,604 million (Dec 31, 2025). The notes specify that CIP is primarily comprised of ongoing facility expansion and **AI infrastructure** that has not yet been placed in service.',
